\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 19. G. macrostylum} Boiss.,{\i  Diagn. Pl. Or. Nov.}{\b  1}({\b 1}): 58 (1843). Rhizome tuberous, but somewhat irregular and lobed. Basal leaves as in {\b 18}. A pair of cauline leaves present; lobes of these and of the lower bracts deeply pinnatifid or pinnatisect. Hairs on pedicels glandular. Sepals 8-11 mm; petals 12-17 mm. Styles 16-18 mm in fruit, the apical 2 mm glabrous and more slender than the rest.{\i  Greece and Albania.} Al Gr.
