\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 20. G. linearilobum} DC. in Lam. & DC.,{\i  Fl. Fr.} ed. 3,{\b  5}: 629 (1815). Rhizome a small, globose tuber. Basal leaves 4-7 cm wide; lobes with usually only 1 linear segment diverging on each side. 1-2 pairs of cauline leaves present; lobes of these and of bracts mostly entire. Hairs on pedicels eglandular. Sepals 5-9 mm; petals 9-15 mm. Styles c. 22 mm in fruit, the apical 2 mm glabrous and more slender than the rest.{\i  Dry places. S.E. Ukraine and S. Russia.} Rs (W, K, E).
