\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 21. G. malviflorum} Boiss. & Reuter, {\i Pugillus} 27 (1852). Rhizome ovoid or oblong, sometimes contorted, scarcely tuber-like. Basal leaves c. 7 cm wide, with usually only 5 deeply pinnatisect lobes, each with 3-4 linear-oblong segments on each side. A pair of cauline leaves present, or sometimes a single leaf. Hairs on pedicels eglandular. Sepals 8-10 mm; petals 17-22 mm. Styles 25 mm in fruit, glabrous below the stigmas but not markedly narrowed.{\i  Rocky hillsides. S. Spain} ({\i Grazalema to Sierra Nevada and northwards to Jaen}). Hs.
