\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 22. G. asphodeloides} Burm. fil.,{\i  Spec. Bot. Geran.} 28 (1759) (incl.{\i  G. tauricum} Rupr.). Perennial, with fleshy, fusiform roots arising from a very short rhizome. Stems 30-75 cm, erect, with deflexed, sometimes glandular hairs. Leaves 4-6 cm wide, divided for 80-85 % of the radius into 5-7 obovate-cuneate, apically 3-fid lobes; segments entire to incise-dentate. Inflorescence diffuse, few-flowered; pedicels slender, glandular-pubescent. Sepals 10 mm, with arista 0·5-1·25 mm; petals c. 15 mm, entire or slightly emarginate, pinkish-lilac with darker veins. Mericarps pubescent, without ridges.{\i  S. Europe, from Sicilia eastwards}. Al Bu Gr It Rm Rs (K) Si Tu.
